East 96th Street, north side, east from a point between Second and First Aves., across the latter to the East River, showing the southeastern corner of the abandoned carbarn of the Second Ave. Railroad Co. The structure partially seen on the right is the New York Railways Co. Power House.

August 13, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

328 East 96th Street, southside between Second and First Avenue, showing P.S. 150.
Board of Education, N.Y.C.
1920.

East 96th Street, west from First Ave. Note the Second and Third Ave. Elevated Lines upon their respective thoroughfares. Partially seen on the right is the abandoned car barn of the Second Ave. Railroad Company.

August 13, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

322-332 East 96th Street, south side, between Second and First Avenues. This is Public School No. 150.
July 16, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(1) First Ave., east side, north from East 96th Street, showing P.S. No. 99 in the center. March 29, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) A portion of the same, showing the area north from East 98th (right) to 100th (extreme left) Streets. The 98th to 99th Streets block, is occupied by a storage yard (N.E. corner of East 98th Street) and a used car lot (S.E. corner of 99th Street). Beyond same, appears P.S. No. 99, extending to 100th Street, with a playground utilizing the First Ave. frontage. Tenements appearing on the extreme left, are on the north side of East 100th Street, east of First Ave.

March 29, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
